### Overview
This strategy simulates how infrastructure scaling can adapt to fluctuating video demand based on forecasted traffic. It uses LSTM_Univariate forecasts and introduces:

- ğŸ”„ Dynamic resource allocation based on predicted views.
- â• A buffer of 0.5 units beyond forecasted requirements to handle minor spikes.
- ğŸš¨ An alerting system to notify when resources are under- or over-provisioned.

---

### ğŸ§® Logic

- **Unit Capacity**: 1 unit supports 50 million views.
- **Buffer**: +0.5 unit added beyond required units.
- **Max Cap**: Optional ceiling of 1B views allocated.

---

### âš ï¸ Alerts

- If actual_views > allocated_capacity â†’ â€œScale-Up Neededâ€
- If actual_views < 50% of allocated_capacity â†’ â€œScale-Down Opportunityâ€

